  34. ‌let read_info name =
  35.   let filename =
  36.     try
  37.       Load_path.find name
  38.     with Not_found ->
  39.       raise(Error(File_not_found name)) in
  40.   let (info, crc) = Compilenv.read_unit_info filename in
  41.   info.ui_force_link <- info.ui_force_link || !Clflags.link_everything;
  42.   (* There is no need to keep the approximation in the .cmxa file,
  43.      since the compiler will go looking directly for .cmx files.
  44.      The linker, which is the only one that reads .cmxa files, does not
  45.      need the approximation. *)
  46.   info.ui_export_info <- default_ui_export_info;
  47.   (Filename.chop_suffix filename ".cmx" ^ ext_obj, (info, crc))

  49. ‌let create_archive file_list lib_name =
  50.   let archive_name = Filename.remove_extension lib_name ^ ext_lib in
  51.   let outchan = open_out_bin lib_name in
  52.   Misc.try_finally
  53.     ~always:(fun () -> close_out outchan)
  54.     ~exceptionally:(fun () -> remove_file lib_name; remove_file archive_name)
  55.     (fun () ->
  56.        output_string outchan cmxa_magic_number;
  57.        let (objfile_list, descr_list) =
  58.          List.split (List.map read_info file_list) in
  59.        List.iter2
  60.          (fun file_name (unit, crc) ->
  61.             Asmlink.check_consistency file_name unit crc)
  62.          file_list descr_list;
  63.        let infos =
  64.          { lib_units = descr_list;
  65.            lib_ccobjs = !Clflags.ccobjs;
  66.            lib_ccopts = !Clflags.all_ccopts } in
  67.        output_value outchan infos;
  68.        if Ccomp.create_archive archive_name objfile_list <> 0
  69.        then raise(Error(Archiver_error archive_name));
